In addition to the Nobel Prize, Luria received the Louisa Gross Horwitz Prize in 1969 with Max Delbrück for their work on the genetics of bacteria and bacteriophage. In 1974, Luria won a National Book Award in the Sciences for 
                Life: The Unfinished Experiment, a work which has been translated into Italian, French, Spanish, German, and Japanese. Other books that Luria published include 
                General Virology; 
                36 Lectures in Biology; 
                A View of Life; and an autobiographical work,
                 A Slot Machine, A Broken Test Tube. He published numerous articles.
